<section xml:id="sec-appB-algebraic-manipulation-and-inequalities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Algebraic manipulation and inequalities</title>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-factoring-patterns">
    <title>Factoring patterns</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^2-b^2=(a-b)(a+b)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^2+2ab+b^2=(a+b)^2}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^2-2ab+b^2=(a-b)^2}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^3-b^3=(a-b)(a^2+ab+b^2)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^3+b^3=(a+b)(a^2-ab+b^2)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{x^2+(p+q)x+pq=(x+p)(x+q)}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-quadratic-formula">
    <title>Quadratic formula</title>

    <p>
      If
      <md>ax^2+bx+c=0, \qquad a\ne0,</md>
      then
      <md>\boxed{x=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      The discriminant is
      <md>\boxed{\Delta=b^2-4ac.}</md>
    </p>

    <table xml:id="appB-alg-tab-discriminant">
      <title>Sign of the discriminant.</title>
      <tabular>
        <row><cell><m>\Delta\gt0</m></cell><cell>two distinct real roots</cell></row>
        <row><cell><m>\Delta=0</m></cell><cell>one repeated real root</cell></row>
        <row><cell><m>\Delta\lt0</m></cell><cell>two complex conjugate roots</cell></row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-completing-the-square">
    <title>Completing the square</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{x^2+bx=\left(x+\frac b2\right)^2-\left(\frac b2\right)^2.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      More generally,
      <md>\boxed{ax^2+bx+c=a\left(x+\frac{b}{2a}\right)^2+c-\frac{b^2}{4a}}</md>
      for <m>a\ne0</m>.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-circle-form">
    <title>Circle form</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(x-h)^2+(y-k)^2=R^2}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Center:
      <md>(h,k).</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Radius:
      <md>R.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-distance-on-the-line">
    <title>Distance on the line</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|x-a|}</md>
      is the distance from <m>x</m> to <m>a</m>.
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|x-a|\lt r \quad\Longleftrightarrow\quad a-r\lt x\lt a+r.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|x-a|\le r \quad\Longleftrightarrow\quad a-r\le x\le a+r.}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|x-a|\gt r \quad\Longleftrightarrow\quad x\lt a-r \text{ or } x\gt a+r.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-absolute-value-rules">
    <title>Absolute value rules</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|ab|=|a|\,|b|}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\left|\frac ab\right|=\frac{|a|}{|b|} \qquad (b\ne0)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{|a+b|\le |a|+|b|}</md>
      This is the triangle inequality.
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\bigl||a|-|b|\bigr|\le |a-b|.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-inequality-rules">
    <title>Inequality rules</title>

    <p>
      Adding or subtracting the same number preserves the inequality:
      <md>a\lt b \quad\Longrightarrow\quad a+c\lt b+c.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Multiplying by a positive number preserves the inequality:
      <md>a\lt b,\ c\gt0 \quad\Longrightarrow\quad ac\lt bc.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Multiplying by a negative number reverses the inequality:
      <md>a\lt b,\ c\lt0 \quad\Longrightarrow\quad ac\gt bc.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-quadratic-inequalities">
    <title>Quadratic inequalities</title>

    <p>
      To solve
      <md>ax^2+bx+c\gt0</md>
      or
      <md>ax^2+bx+c\lt0,</md>
      use this process:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li><p>Find the zeros.</p></li>
      <li><p>Put the zeros on the number line.</p></li>
      <li><p>Test one point in each interval.</p></li>
      <li><p>Include endpoints only for <m>\le</m> or <m>\ge</m>.</p></li>
    </ol>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-exponent-rules">
    <title>Exponent rules</title>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^m a^n=a^{m+n}}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\frac{a^m}{a^n}=a^{m-n} \qquad (a\ne0)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(a^m)^n=a^{mn}}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{(ab)^n=a^n b^n}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^{-n}=\frac1{a^n} \qquad (a\ne0)}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{a^{1/n}=\sqrt[n]{a}}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-logarithm-rules">
    <title>Logarithm rules</title>

    <p>
      For <m>a\gt0</m>, <m>b\gt0</m>, and <m>r\in\mathbb R</m>,
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\ln(ab)=\ln a+\ln b}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\ln\left(\frac ab\right)=\ln a-\ln b}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\ln(a^r)=r\ln a}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{e^{\ln a}=a}</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\ln(e^x)=x}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appB-alg-common-warnings">
    <title>Common warnings</title>

    <warning>
      <p>Do not divide by a quantity unless it is known to be nonzero.</p>

      <p>Do not take square roots of both sides of an inequality without tracking signs.</p>

      <p>
        <md>x^2\gt9</md>
        means
        <md>x\lt-3 \quad\text{or}\quad x\gt3,</md>
        not just <m>x\gt3</m>.
      </p>

      <p>
        The identity
        <md>\sqrt{x^2}=|x|</md>
        is usually safer than writing <m>\sqrt{x^2}=x</m>.
      </p>
    </warning>
  </subsection>
</section>
